cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY 

The paper discusses the dragonfly algorithm, which is a heuristic optimization algorithm used in machine learning, image processing, wireless, and networking. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the algorithm's ability to optimize real-world problems, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The algorithm's application in image processing suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the algorithm's use in wireless and networking applications suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control).
